extends layout


block body
  .container.narrow

    .page-header
      h1 Git Miner
      .lead Dig into guts of git history


    h3 How it works:

    p This tool doesn't need an access to your repository. It needs only one thing - your git log.

    ul
      li Navigate in your terminal to the directory where your repo is placed.
      li Copy one of those snippets from the box below, and execute it in the terminal:
        p To download log parser script using cURL:
        pre curl -s https://gitminer.com/parser.sh | bash
        p or using Wget:
        pre wget -qO- https://gitminer.com/parser.sh | bash
      li Wait until it finishes parsing your git history and upload it to the server for analyzing.
      li Follow the link to receive the history report.

    .alert.alert-info
      | You can check sample report for the repository of
      a(href="/report/wn36t", target="_blank") Google v8 repo
      |  or
      a(href="/report/1jle2x", target="_blank") lodash nodejs module.


